programme.title: Dog Soldier TV
programme.desc: Part 2. Sterling Hollywood Justice takes the Dog Soldier on a Texas hunting spree. High racks, Optical Dynamics lights and mesquite are the combination of predator perfection.(n)

programme.title: BuckVentures Outdoors
programme.desc: Evan Green, Kord Etbauer and Shane Roy head to Indiana to bowfish for bigheads.(n)

programme.title: Canada in the Rough
programme.sub-title: Bulls and Bears on the Rock
programme.desc: Paul Beasley heads to Newfoundland to spot-and-stalk big bull moose and black bears with Island Safaris.(n)

programme.title: Western Extreme
programme.desc: Jim is in Mexico deer hunting.(n)

programme.title: Trained Assassins
programme.desc: Cragg Fitz continues his quest chasing whitetails in Nebraska with Terry. Slade Priest will be hunting his property in Mississippi, while Blake heads back to Illinois to try to fill his muzzleloader tag.(n)

programme.title: Avian-X TV
programme.desc: Part 2. Josh and JR still have two tags left to fill at Rut-N-Strut Outfitters in Oklahoma.(n)

programme.title: Predator Pursuit
programme.sub-title: Red River Shoot Out Part Two
programme.desc: Part 2. Jeff travels to Oklahoma with Rafter F Hunts for a mix bag of thermal hog hunting at night and predator calling in the daytime.(n)

programme.title: Waterfowl Obsession
programme.desc: Scott Butz looks back at a couple of his favorite hunts from years past.(n)

programme.title: Xtreme Crappie Angler
programme.desc: Karl is fishing with small spinnerbaits for big black crappie on weedbeds in early summer with B'n'M Crappie Wizard poles and light lines.(n)

programme.title: Fishing University
programme.desc: Charlie and Ray welcome guests, Matt Cashion, owner, and Paul Benson, national sales manager of Cashion Rods, featuring the newest line of bass fishing rods on Lake Amistad in Del Rio, Texas.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Stan Potts crosses the Canadian border in search of bull moose; Dr. James Kroll talks warm-season food plots; and Jeremy Moore completes a three-part series on shed dog training.(n)

programme.title: Sporting Chef
programme.desc: Chef Scott cooks live Dungeness crabs; Susie makes elk lettuce wraps; Brad's got duck; Stacy makes a different kind of pie; Tommy cooks his favorite fish; and Buddy makes cakes.(n)

programme.title: The Game Chef
programme.desc: Angelo hunts for tahr, then cooks up deviled tahr, tahr Moroccan stew and stuffed tahr backstraps.(n)

programme.title: The Ontario Experience
programme.desc: Troy Lindner flies into doubleheader walleye action and a classic Canadian shore lunch at Pine Portage Lodge in Ontario's Algoma region.(n)

programme.title: Savage Outdoors *
programme.desc: Mike Stroff is back in Iowa hunting with Coal Camp Outfitters with his Savage Slug gun. This is a hunt Mike has done before and Coal Camp has produced some of his best whitetail bucks over the years.(n)

programme.title: Made for the Outdoors
programme.desc: Lindsey sees how duck boats and tractor attachments get made.(n)

programme.title: BuckVentures Outdoors *
programme.desc: Jeff Danker and Daniel McVay dive into the effects that coyotes and hogs have on growing and hunting mature whitetail bucks.(n)

programme.title: Major League Bowhunter
programme.desc: Brandon Danker has a giant within range during late season in Kansas. After filming and taking the largest deer of his life the previous year, Brandon has his sights set on yet another giant on the same farm.(n)

programme.title: Dominant Bucks
programme.desc: The team discusses do-it-yourself rut tactics.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.sub-title: A Room With a View - Part I
programme.desc: Part 1. Gordon Whittington heads home to Texas for whitetail action; Dr. Deer discusses timber management and thermal cover; and Jeremy Moore explores pitfalls on puppy training.(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.desc: The staff slides into seasonal slay-them mode as they sample ice-out lake trout in Rocky Mountain high country, tussle with behemoth white sturgeon in heavy current and put the crank to peak-period largemouths.(n)

programme.title: Fishing University
programme.desc: Charlie and Ray are joined by Kevin Lamar, CEO of Soft Science Shoes, and Ginger Lamar, Board of Directors, as they demonstrate their great boat shoes while fishing for those huge Wheeler Lake bass.(n)

programme.title: Xtreme Crappie Angler
programme.desc: Early spring crappie, days after ice-out in 39 degree water, and Karl & Seabass are provoking strikes by popping and stopping the bobbers with B'n'M poles.(n)

programme.title: On the Water with Hank Parker
programme.desc: Hank Parker heads to Lake Ontario for some awesome fishing.(n)

programme.title: Steve's Outdoor Adventures
programme.desc: Special Youth Hunter Amber Mozingo who is battling Cystic Fibrosis travels to Oregon with Camo Dreams and Tombo Martin from Buck Commander to hunt elk with Steve West during the peak of the rut.(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: Mike Schoby joins his buddies, Jon Dubin and Jeff Johnston, on the island of Lanai for a deer hunt, Hawaiian-style. Join the boys as they sample island life and live it up at the Four Season's hotel.(n)

programme.title: Long Range Pursuit
programme.desc: Predators didn't stand a chance with the extermination squad on the mission. The new Gunwerks Co-pilot rifle takes center stage and shows why this gun was designed to be the passenger on a run and gun mission.(n)

programme.title: Gun Stories *
programme.desc: We continue our look back at the season's highlights, including The Rolling Block and The Model 29.(n)

programme.title: Guns & Ammo TV
programme.desc: Technology has advanced to the point where manufacturers are building guns with polymer foundations, like Taurus' new Spectrum & S&W's M&P Shield EZ. Crimson Trace has new LaserGuards & we take a look at unique switch-barrel technology.(n)

programme.title: GunVenture
programme.sub-title: A Day at the NRA Show
programme.desc: The crew heads to the 2017 NRA annual meetings in Atlanta. Follow along as they walk the show floor to check out some new guns and talk with friends. Also: extra fun with a silencer shoot, a Father's Day promo, some radio shows and more.(n)

programme.title: Fish Hard
programme.desc: FLW Tour pro Mark Rose and friend Chris Brown fish the waters of a place called the Peach Orchard. Mark Rose and Strike King's Allan Ranson also fish the waters of Pickwick Lake, while Mark Zona flips docks on Portage Lake.(n)

programme.title: Livin' the Dream With Captain Jimmy Nelson
programme.desc: Jimmy and Luiza are fishing out of The Plantation on Crystal River and have an awesome day off-shore catching grouper, snapper and amberjacks.(n)

programme.title: Extreme Outer Limits TV
programme.desc: Bob and Chris Beck hunt antelope in Wyoming.(n)

programme.title: Grace, Camo & Lace
programme.desc: Part 2. The Armstrong family is still in Nebraska on their spring archery turkey hunt.(n)

programme.title: Skull Bound TV
programme.desc: Jana Waller scours the Montana backcountry for elk with her bow. The highs and lows of DIY hunting are all captured on this episode as Jana arrows her biggest bull to date in the heart of grizzly country.(n)

programme.title: Winchester Deadly Passion
programme.desc: Summer is the ideal time to hit the water and spend some quality time bowfishing, but Melissa takes it up a notch by going after everything from tuna to shark to alligator gar.(n)

programme.title: Jim Shockey's Uncharted
programme.desc: Jim returns to Russia to traverse frigid rivers and hills in search of Siberian Brown bears.(n)

programme.title: Beyond Rubicon
programme.desc: Two brothers hunt elk in the Gila National Forest and are having a difficult time getting close enough to capture the elk on video, much less shooting them with their bows.(n)

programme.title: Night Crew
programme.desc: Night Crew beats a 100-year flood to get it done.(n)
